HOUSE CONCURRENT RESOLUTION NO. 8
BY REPRESENTATIVE BAYHAM
COMMENDATIONS: Commends Drew Brees for being elected to the Pro Football Hall
of Fame
1 A CONCURRENT RESOLUTION
2 To commend Drew Brees for being elected to the Pro Football Hall of Fame.
3 WHEREAS, Drew Brees was a standout high-school football player in Austin,
4 Texas, leading his team to a state title and receiving the Texas 5A Offensive Player of the
5 Year honors in 1996; and
6 WHEREAS, as a three-year starting quarterback at Purdue University in West
7 Lafayette, Indiana, Mr. Brees set both school and Big Ten Conference records in nearly
8 every major passing category, including passing yards and touchdowns; in his senior season,
9 he led the Boilermakers to their first Rose Bowl berth in thirty-four years and finished third
10 in the voting for the Heisman Trophy; and
11 WHEREAS, Mr. Brees was selected by the San Diego Chargers with the first pick
12 of the second round of the 2001 NFL Draft and became the franchise's starting quarterback
13 in his second season; during the 2004 season, he led the Chargers to a surprising 12-4 record
14 and received the NFL's Comeback Player of the Year Award and Pro Bowl honors; and
15 WHEREAS, Mr. Brees signed a free agent deal with New Orleans before the 2006
16 season and helped lead the Saints to a 10-6 record and a berth in the NFC Championship
17 Game; he led the league in passing yards that year and received first-team All-Pro honors
18 for his performance; in 2008, he tallied 5,069 passing yards and was voted to participate in
19 the Pro Bowl; and
20 WHEREAS, during the 2009 season, Mr. Brees set an NFL record by completing
21 70.6 percent of his passes and led the Saints to a franchise-record 13-0 start to the season;
