1 most importantly, he guided the team to its first-ever Super Bowl berth in Super Bowl XLIV,
2 which resulted in a Saints victory over the Indianapolis Colts; during the Super Bowl, he
3 completed a thirty-two passes and passed for two hundred eighty-eight yards and two
4 touchdowns and was named the Super Bowl MVP; and
5 WHEREAS, Mr. Brees had another record-setting season in 2011, breaking Dan
6 Marino's single-season passing yardage record by finishing the season with 5,476 passing
7 yards; he also broke his own league record for passing completion percentage by completing
8 71.2 percent of his passes, and he established an all-time NFL record by passing for more
9 than three hundred yards in thirteen consecutive games; and
10 WHEREAS, in 2012, Mr. Brees broke Johnny Unitas' record for most consecutive
11 games with a touchdown pass, finishing with at least one touchdown pass in fifty-four
12 consecutive regular season games; he also finished the 2012 season with 5,177 passing yards
13 and a league-high forty-three touchdown passes; and
14 WHEREAS, in 2013, Mr. Brees passed for a league-high 5,162 yards, and in 2014,
15 he finished with 4,952 passing yards; he led the league in passing yardage during the 2015
16 and 2016 seasons, finishing with 4,870 yards and 5,280 yards, respectively; and
17 WHEREAS, in 2017, Mr. Brees helped guide the Saints to an eleven-win season and
18 the NFC South division title; he began the 2018 season in historic fashion, setting the NFL
19 record for all-time pass completions and all-time passing yards; he finished the 2018 season
20 with 3,992 passing yards and thirty-two touchdown passes; he also set a new NFL single-
21 season record by completing 74.4 percent of his pass attempts; in December 2019, he broke
22 the NFL record for career touchdown passes; and
23 WHEREAS, Mr. Brees announced his retirement on March 14, 2021, and he was
24 announced as a first ballot inductee into the Pro Football Hall of Fame at the NFL Honors
25 ceremony on February 5, 2026; and
26 WHEREAS, Drew Brees is an iconic quarterback who, through his achievements as
27 a New Orleans Saint, has become a part of the cultural fabric of the Crescent City and the
28 state of Louisiana; he is truly most deserving of the highest recognition.
29 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Legislature of Louisiana does hereby
30 commend Drew Brees for being elected to the Pro Football Hall of Fame; does hereby
